PING SCAN : -sn

    CHECK IF LIVE IP IN RANGE : nmap -sn 192.168.54.34-115

    CHECK IF LIVE SCAN SUBNETS : nmap -sn 192.168.45.0/24

    CHECK IF LIVE SCAN HOST : nmap -sn Example.com_OR_IP

LIST SCAN TARGETS : nmap -sL 192.169.12.0/24


CONNECT SCAN FOR 3 WAY HANDSHAKE COMPLETE : nmap -sT 192.168.0.0/16

SYN STEALTH SCAN FOR PARTIAL HANDSHAKE : nmap -sS 192.168.0.0/16

SCAN FOR UDP SERVICES : nmap -sU 192.168.0.0/16

SCAN COMMON 100 PORTS : nmap -F 192.168.0.0/16

SCAN PORT FROM 1 TO 97 : nmap -p1-97 192.168.0.0/16

SCAN PORT FROM 1 TO 99 : nmap -p-99 192.168.0.0/16

SCAN ALL PORTS : nmap -p- 192.168.0.0/16


DETECT OPERATING SYSTEM : nmap -sS -O IP_Addr

DETECT SERVICE VERSION : nmap -sV IP_Addr

DETECT OS, SERVICE VERSON TRACEROUTE AND MORE : nmap -A IP_Addr

SCAN FOR HOSTS APPEAR DOWN : nmap -Pn IP_Addr


SCAN TIME TEMPLATE : nmap -T4 OR -T aggressive

    T0 (paranoid)	
    T1 (sneaky)	
    T2 (polite)	
    T3 (normal)	
    T4 (aggressive)
    T5 (insane)

    --min-parallelism <numprobes> :	Minimum number of parallel probes
    --max-parallelism <numprobes> : maximum numbe rof parallel probes

    --min-rate <number> : minum rate
    --max-rate <number>	: maximum rate (packets/second)

    --host-timeout : Maximum amount of time to wait for a target host


VERBOSE : nmap -sS IP_Addr -v { v1 v2 v3 v4 OR v vv vvv vvvv}

DEBUG : nmap -sS IP_Addr -d {d1 to d9 }


SAVE SCAN REPORT : nmap -sS IP -oA File0

    -oN <filename> - Normal output
    -oX <filename> - XML output
    -oG <filename> - grep-able output (useful for grep and awk)
    -oA <basename> - Output in all major formats

    